                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Why did we create a own platform?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">The reason why we decided to build our own platform is because we want 100% control over
                    our content, our infrastructure and prices. We believe this is the best way to guarantee quality.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">What does Devscorch stand for?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">The name Devscorch is inspired by the words development and scorch. Development because we
                    are all developers and scorch because our code is burning 24/7 </p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Why does Devscorch not support social login? </h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">We don't support social media login because of privacy reasons. We believe that social networks
                    don't need to know everything about you.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Does Devscorch use third party Analytics or trackers?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">No! Devscorch does not contain any third party trackers, Analytics software or beacons. 
                    We believe your information is yours only and should stay yours only.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">What does Devscorch use for analysing user behavior?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">We dont really analyse user behavior on our platform at this time. But we are building our
                    own analytics system in our backend. This only analyses most watched courses and future course predictions.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Why is registering and login a bit slow sometimes?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">This is because of the user encryption. The encryption algorithm we use for encryption
                    is designed to be slow and strong.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">What does Devscorch use for user information encryption?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">At Devscorch we use BCrypt. BCrypt is a one way hashing algorithm which is designed to be slow. This
                    makes decrypting user information in case of a hack almost impossible. Because it would need a lot of processing power to decrypt.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Which technologies are used for Devscorch?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">The Devscorch platform us build using: Vapor, Swift, Bootstrap, Javascript, LEAF and
                    plain HTML and CSS.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Where is the Devscorch platform hosted?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">The Devscorch platform is hosted on our own servers which are placed in Data centers in Europe.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Why isn't Devscorch using Firebase, AWS, Azure or other cloud providers?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">This has two main reasons actually. First because of privacy reasons. Other companies don't need to
                    know what we do, what our users do or what we work on. Second reason is because we like coding and setting up our own 
                    infrastructure.</p>

                    <h6 class="faq-h6">Which payment provider is Devscorch using?</h6>
                    <p class="faq-p">At Devscorch we use Stripe for handling our payments. Stripe is worlds most used payment provider because
                    it is secure, fast and really reliable.</p>
